[30;1m27 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m28 | [0m[35mdef _binary_eer_compute(fpr: Tensor, tpr: Tensor) -> Tensor:[0m
[30;1m29 | [0m[35m    """Compute Equal Error Rate (EER) for binary classification task."""[0m
[30;1m30 | [0m[35m    diff = fpr - (1 - tpr)[0m
[30;1m31 | [0m[35m    idx = torch.argmin(torch.abs(diff))[0m
[30;1m32 | [0m[35m    return (fpr[idx] + (1 - tpr[idx])) / 2[0m
[30;1m33 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m510 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m511 | [0m[35mdef _multilabel_confusion_matrix_update(preds: Tensor, target: Tensor, num_labels: int) -> Tensor:[0m
[30;1m512 | [0m[35m    """Compute the bins to update the confusion matrix with."""[0m
[30;1m513 | [0m[35m    unique_mapping = ((2 * target + preds) + 4 * torch.arange(num_labels, device=preds.device)).flat[0m
[30;1m514 | [0m[35m    unique_mapping = unique_mapping[unique_mapping >= 0][0m
[30;1m515 | [0m[35m    bins = _bincount(unique_mapping, minlength=4 * num_labels)[0m

[30;1m324 | [0m[35mdef _multiclass_confusion_matrix_update(preds: Tensor, target: Tensor, num_classes: int) -> Tensor:[0m
[30;1m325 | [0m[35m    """Compute the bins to update the confusion matrix with."""[0m

[30;1m148 | [0m[35mdef _binary_confusion_matrix_update(preds: Tensor, target: Tensor) -> Tensor:[0m
[30;1m149 | [0m[35m    """Compute the bins to update the confusion matrix with."""[0m
[30;1m150 | [0m[35m    unique_mapping = (target * 2 + preds).to(torch.long)[0m
[30;1m151 | [0m[35m    bins = _bincount(unique_mapping, minlength=4)[0m
[30;1m152 | [0m[35m    return bins.reshape(2, 2)[0m

[30;1m64 | [0m[35mclass RetrievalPrecisionRecallCurve(Metric):[0m
[30;1m65 | [0m[35m    """Compute precision-recall pairs for different k (from 1 to `max_k`).[0m
[30;1m66 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m67 | [0m[35m    In a ranked retrieval context, appropriate sets of retrieved documents are naturally given by th[0m
[30;1m68 | [0m[35m    documents. Recall is the fraction of relevant documents retrieved among all the relevant documen[0m
[30;1m69 | [0m[35m    fraction of relevant documents among all the retrieved documents. For each such set, precision a[0m
[30;1m70 | [0m[35m    can be plotted to give a recall-precision curve.[0m

[30;1m345 | [0m[35m    r"""Compute Area Under the Receiver Operating Characteristic Curve (`ROC AUC`_) for multilabel t[0m
[30;1m346 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m347 | [0m[35m    The AUROC score summarizes the ROC curve into an single number that describes the performance of[0m

[30;1m94 | [0m[35m    max_area: Tensor = tensor(max_fpr, device=_device)[0m
[30;1m95 | [0m[35m    # Add a single point at max_fpr and interpolate its tpr value[0m
[30;1m96 | [0m[35m    stop = torch.bucketize(max_area, fpr, out_int32=True, right=True)[0m
[30;1m97 | [0m[35m    weight = (max_area - fpr[stop - 1]) / (fpr[stop] - fpr[stop - 1])[0m
[30;1m98 | [0m[35m    interp_tpr: Tensor = torch.lerp(tpr[stop - 1], tpr[stop], weight)[0m

[30;1m27 | [0m[35m    Critical success index (also known as the threat score) is a statistic used weather forecasting [0m
[30;1m28 | [0m[35m    forecast performance over inputs binarized at a specified threshold. It is defined as:[0m
[30;1m29 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m30 | [0m[35m    .. math:: \text{CSI} = \frac{\text{TP}}{\text{TP}+\text{FN}+\text{FP}}[0m
[30;1m31 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m22 | [0m[35mdef retrieval_hit_rate(preds: Tensor, target: Tensor, top_k: Optional[int] = None) -> Tensor:[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    """Compute the hit rate for information retrieval.[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m26 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m46 | [0m[35m    All ``indexes``, ``preds`` and ``target`` must have the same dimension and will be flatten at th[0m
[30;1m47 | [0m[35m    so that for example, a tensor of shape ``(N, M)`` is treated as ``(N * M, )``. Predictions will [0m
[30;1m48 | [0m[35m    ``indexes`` and then will be computed as the mean of the metric over each query.[0m
[30;1m49 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m435 | [0m[35m        # extract predicted class index for computing accuracy[0m
[30;1m436 | [0m[35m        preds = preds.argmax(dim=-1)[0m
[30;1m437 | [0m[35m        assert preds.shape == target.shape[0m

[30;1m439 | [0m[35m        self.correct += torch.sum(preds == target)[0m
[30;1m440 | [0m[35m        self.total += target.numel()[0m
